tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  40,28,"All these forms of travel are possible due to the grace of God and if man consciously reflected, he would prostrate himself before God and never develop an attitude of arrogance."
  40,31,"(a) Behind a man are his actions and before him lies the Day of Reckoning. Life, in other words, is a journey from the world of actions towards the world of results. This is a very crucial state of affairs. If a man actually realises his position, he will start trembling. But he does not consider this nor does any sign open his eyes. He tries to justify his actions by false interpretations until the day he dies."